{
  "texts": [
    "The temporal dynamics in each neuron endows SNNs with the capability to memorize historic information.",
    "In a vanilla LIF neuron, the membrane potential, i.e., u, can be viewed as the memory of historic information.",
    "Long-term memory can be achieved by configuring a large timing factor on the membrane potential, i.e., β, for slowing the membrane potential decaying.",
    "However, we argue that a vanilla LIF neuron cannot truly memorize information for a long time even with a large β value due to the reset mechanism of the membrane potential every time the neuron fires a spike.",
    "Fortunately, the proposed DH-LIF succeeds in preserving long-term information owing to the multicompartment modeling."
  ]
}